content: When a user is deactivated, the recipes in which they made the most recent modification are unscheduled to prevent unnecessary runs. A recipe is automatically unscheduled when its Last Modified By user is deactivated. To avoid this situation, check the recipesâ€™ Last Modified By column in Data Manager before deactivating the user. Reschedule the recipes that the user modified. If a recipe is unscheduled, create a schedule with an active user. Unscheduling when a user is deactivated also affects dataflows.
title: Preventing Recipe Unscheduling in CRM Analytics
